name: Youth
description:
Time flies, flows and sinks.

This picture was taken on a spring time morning in Amsterdam in 2014 from my kayak.

Reflected in the water is the famous landmark De Magere Brug.

The name "Magere Brug" means "Skinny Bridge". Legend has it that a young girl had the bridge built because her sister lived on the other side of the canal - so they could see each other more often.

Couples who kiss on Magere Brug stay together forever - at least that's what the legend says. We can't find a better place to kiss and it's definitely worth a try.

The white baby swan feather, floating fragile and untouched before an inevitable wave on the most busy spot of Amsterdam will engulf it, to me stands for innocence and a first step into the future which lies ahead, whatever it may bring.
